        <h2>Hip Flexors. What are those??</h2>
        <p>Hip flexors connect your leg muscles to your abdominal muscles, and are very important for walking. When humans age, the hip flexors can deteriorate due to less physical activity and due to sitting too long. This can lead to the "shuffling" effect when you are older.</p>

        <p>Once you've reached "The Shuffle" stage, it is pretty difficult to regain strength back in your hip flexors without some serious work. I try to prevent a lot of this deterioration by doing this stretch every day. I like to do mine in the mornings right after a short 10 minute walk. I also try to do it before bed too (along with other light stretching).</p>

