<h2>What I do</h2>

<ol>
    <li>First I sit on the floor (carpet is usually more comfortable to me than the hardwood floor) with one leg out, and my other leg close to my chest. I try to keep my back as straight as possible.</li>
    <li>I then squeeze my stomach and try to lift my leg off the ground. I hold this position for one second, then slowly lower it to the ground.</li>
    <li>I started off doing 4 raises with each leg. My hip flexors were initially pretty weak and it made this exercise pretty difficult. I always start off slow and raise my legs in a controlled manner.</li>
    <li>Every week or every other week, I try to increase my repetitions by 1 to achieve progressive overload.</li>
</ol>
